ace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20anticipates%20the%20probe%20will%20experience%20temperatures%20of%201%2C800%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20which%20shouldn't%20be%20an%20issue%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-parker-solar-probe-heat-temperature-radiation-survival-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espacecraft's%20protective%20heat%20shield%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20designed%20to%20withstand%20temperatures%20over%202%2C500%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%203.8%20million%20miles%20is%20far%20by%20Earth's%20standards%2C%20but%20it's%20ridiculously%20close%20when%20you're%20out%20in%20deep%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20like%20if%20you%20put%20the%20Earth%20and%20sun%20at%20opposite%20ends%20of%20an%20American%20football%20field%3A%20%26quot%3BParker%20Solar%20Probe%20is%20on%20the%204-yard%20line%20approaching%20the%20sun%2C%26quot%3B%20Joe%20Westlake%2C%20Director%20of%20NASA's%20Science%20Mission%20Directorate's%20Heliophysics%20Division%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DEAg2HQmDL3A%26ab_channel%3D6abcPhiladelphia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%206abc%20Philadelphia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20getting%20so%20close%20that%20we're%20actually%20in%20the%20sun's%20upper%20atmosphere.%20We're%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-on-mission-to-touch-the-sun-in-milestone-for-space-exploration-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etouching%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20humanity's%20first%20mission%20to%20a%20star%2C%26quot%3B%20Westlake%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e73ea5a-a52d-4cac-a97e-85496c67d863%5C%22%3EThe%20moment%20NASA%20has%20been%20waiting%20for%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Christmas%20Eve%20flyby%20is%20the%20moment%20the%20mission%20has%20been%20building%20up%20to%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20close%20approach%20is%20only%20possible%20because%20of%20the%20mission's%20orbital%20design%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20NASA%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20spacecraft%20had%20to%20shed%20a%20lot%20of%20orbital%20energy%20to%20get%20this%20close%20to%20the%20sun%2C%20so%20that's%20why%20it%20took%20several%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%20the%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe%2C%20about%20the%20size%20of%20a%20small%20car%2C%20has%20made%20increasingly%20close%20flybys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20September%202020%2C%20it%20flew%20within%208.4%20million%20miles%20of%20the%20solar%20surface.%20By%20September%202023%2C%20it%20reached%20within%204.5%20million%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20spacecraft%20makes%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-orbiter-closest-photos-videos-ever-taken-of-the-sun-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20approaches%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20cuts%20communication%20with%20Earth%20and%20flies%20autonomously%2C%20guiding%20itself%20through%20the%20sun's%20harsh%20upper%20atmosphere%20until%20it's%20far%20enough%20away%20to%20reestablish%20coms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20last%20heard%20from%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe%20on%20December%2022%20and%20expects%20to%20hear%20from%20it%20again%20around%20midnight%20between%20Thursday%20and%20Friday%2C%20Nour%20Rawafi%2C%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe%20project%20scientist%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20Applied%20Physics%20Lab%2C%20said%20during%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D25pIyNdFBi0%26ab_channel%3DNASA.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20livestream.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20flying%20so%20close%20to%20the%20sun%20doesn't%20hold%20any%20promise%20of%20discovering%20alien%20life%20there%20or%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20future%20crewed%20missions%20to%20walk%20on%20the%20solar%20surface%2C%20the%20Parker%20Solar%20Probe's%20mission%20is%2C%20arguably%2C%20more%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20this%20historic%20mission%20and%20how%20it%20could%20help%20humanity%20solve%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d7a6c20-dcf2-4d88-84f9-99370da749cc%5C%22%3EParker%20Solar%20Probe%20is%20helping%20us%20answer%20the%20big%20questions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20appear%20calm%20and%20quiet%20from%20far%20away%2C%20but%20the%20sun%20is%20a%20turbulent%20sphere%20of%20activity.%20It's%20got%20solar%20flares%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiant-solar-eruption-hits-earth-earlier-than-forecast-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20eruptions%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20fire%20fast-moving%2C%20charged%20particles%20deep%20into%20our%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20that%20activity%2C%20we%20would%20not%20exist.%20That%20activity%20is%20really%20necessary%20for%20life%20to%20kick%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Rawafi%20said%20during%20NASA's%20livestream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20on%20a%20grand%20scale%2C%20understanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelio-year-sun-solar-system-probe-eclipse-events-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20our%20sun%20works%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20us%20better%20understand%20how%20life%20originated%20on%20Earth%20and%20where%20it%20might%20exist%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20by%20studying%20our%20own%20star%20up%20close%2C%20we%20can%20learn%20how%20other%20stars%20in%20the%20universe%20interact%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20billions%20and%20billions%20of%20other%20planets%20that%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20like%20our%20own%20planets%2C%26quot%3B%20Alex%20Young%2C%20associate%20director%20for%20science%20communication%20in%20NASA's%20Heliophysics%20Science%20Division%2C%20said%20during%20the%20livestream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ede3d894-ba1e-4f52-8f6a-f50f5e6628d6%5C%22%3EWishing%20