arly%20Sunday%20morning%20local%20time%2C%20the%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Gettysburg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-missile-cruiser-super-hornet-friendly-fire-incident-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emistakenly%20fired%20on%20an%20F%2FA-18%20Super%20Hornet%3C%2Fa%3E%20flying%20above%20the%20Red%20Sea%2C%20downing%20the%20carrier-based%20fighter%20in%20what%20the%20US%20military%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20apparent%20case%20of%20friendly%20fire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Central%20Command%20said%20that%20two%20naval%20aviators%20ejected%20safely%20from%20the%20aircraft%20and%20were%20recovered%20by%20the%20Navy.%20It%20added%20that%20an%20initial%20assessment%20suggests%20one%20of%20the%20crew%20members%20sustained%20minor%20injuries.%20A%20two-seater%20F%2FA-18%20typically%20has%20a%20pilot%20and%20weapons%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECentcom%2C%20which%20oversees%20US%20forces%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20said%20the%20incident%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20the%20result%20of%20hostile%20fire%2C%20and%20a%20full%20investigation%20is%20underway.%26quot%3B%20It%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20more%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223868%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20F%2FA-18F%20Super%20Hornet%20takes%20off%20from%20the%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Harry%20S.%20Truman%20in%20December.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6769bd28a3e82c79120411a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222763%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20F%2FA-18F%20Super%20Hornet%20takes%20off%20from%20the%20flight%20deck%20of%20the%20aircraft%20carrier%20USS%20Harry%20S.%20Truman%20in%20December.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFriendly-fire%20engagements%20aren't%20uncommon%20occurrences%20in%20combat%2C%20especially%20high-intensity%20fights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Gulf%20War%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20an%20A-10%20Warthog%20killed%20nine%20British%20soldiers%20when%20the%20ground-attack%20aircraft%20opened%20fire%20on%20their%20armored%20personnel%20carriers%2C%20mistaking%20them%20for%20Iraqi%20vehicles.%20A%20few%20years%20later%2C%20F-15s%20shot%20down%20two%20Black%20Hawks%20on%20a%20humanitarian%20mission%2C%20killing%2026%20people.%20The%20pilots%20mistook%20the%20helicopters%20for%20Iraqi%20targets%20they%20thought%20were%20violating%20a%20%26quot%3Bno%20fly%26quot%3B%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20numerous%20examples%20across%20military%20conflicts%2C%20a%20more%20recent%20incident%20being%20a%20US%20airstrike%20in%20Afghanistan%20that%20killed%20five%20American%20servicemembers%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBradley%20Martin%2C%20a%20retired%20Navy%20surface%20warfare%20captain%2C%20said%20friendly-fire%20incidents%20are%20%26quot%3Blikely%20to%20eventually%20occur%20in%20the%20complicated%20and%20rapidly%20changing%20environment%20of%20air%20defense.%26quot%3B%20There%20are%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20things%20that%20can%20go%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFriendly%20and%20enemy%20aircraft%20can%20be%20in%20the%20engagement%20areas.%20Identification%20systems%20can%20malfunction%2C%26quot%3B%20Martin%2C%20now%20a%20senior%20policy%20researcher%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BFriendly%20aircraft%20profiles%20can%20look%20like%20threat%20profiles.%20And%20certainly%2C%20human%20error%20can%20enter%20into%20the%20equation.%20Operators%20may%20have%20minutes%20or%20even%20seconds%20to%20make%20a%20determination%20and%2C%20mistakes%20occur.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226088%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20guided-missile%20cruiser%20USS%20Gettysburg%20sails%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20in%20December.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6769bd7d9de00e389eb31771%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224059%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20guided-